FEATURES             Location/Qualifiers
     protein_domain  1..14
                     /label="SpyTag002"
                     /synonym="SpyTag 002"
                     /synonym="SpyTag002"
                     /note="Second-generation 14-aa peptide tag (VPTIVMVDAYKRYK)
                     derived from the CnaB2 immunoglobulin-like domain of
                     Streptococcus pyogenes fibronectin-binding protein FbaB,
                     evolved from the original SpyTag (AHIVMVDAYKPTK) by
                     phage-display selection plus rational design. SpyTag002
                     differs from SpyTag at 4/13 shared residues and carries one
                     extra N-terminal residue. On mixing with its protein
                     partner SpyCatcher002 it forms a spontaneous, irreversible
                     intermolecular isopeptide (amide) bond (reactive Asp;
                     partner Lys; catalysed by SpyCatcher Glu77); single
                     Asp->Ala (DA) mutation abolishes the reaction. Fusable at
                     the N-terminus or C-terminus. Backwards-compatible with the
                     parental SpyCatcher."
                     /citation=[1]
                     /citation=[2]
                     /citation=[3]
